<tr><td align="left" valign="bottom" width="98%"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/toptab.gif" width="98" height="10" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0"></td><td align="left" valign="bottom" width="22">&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td bgcolor="#3F403F" width="98%" class="cheader"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></td><td bgcolor="3F403F" valign="top" align="right" width="22"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/topcorner.gif" width="23" height="22" border="0" vspace="0" hspace="0" align="right"></td></tr>
<tr><td width="98%" colspan=2><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" class="cbody">
<tr><td><font class="h1font"> Brandon Ruck - Player Created V9<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/starwarsccg/gfx/theme1/star.gif" width="19" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.87)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175'>Scott "CRingwell" Lingrell</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=175&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> April 20, 2005</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> When you get the opportunity to create a completely original card, you start to think of all of the possible things you yourself would like to do in the game. I, myself, decided to look over past V-cards by players, and the main thing I noticed was that no one had ever created a weapon. I also have always wanted Yoda to have a lightsaber after seeing Episode 2, so it just made sense that my card be Jedi Lightsaber (V).<br />
<br />
The design of this card has gone through a few changes along the way as the playtesting went on. Originally, I had wanted it to run completely around Yoda. I want to reflect how Yoda was able to fight in Episode 2, and the fact that even though ALL of the Jedi were wiped out by the Empire and Vader. Yoda could NOT be killed and just died of old age on Dagobah. That premise is where the three destinies came from. It made sense to give him an advantage when in a defensive battle because that is what Jedi are all about, &quot;Knowledge and Defense.&quot; In the original design, I had it that unless the target was a Dark Jedi, Yoda would cause any hit target to be Lost and not just hit. This idea was meant to kill off normally weaker characters that in the story would never be able to kill Yoda, but it got changed to droids because it was found to be WAY too broken. The ability to kill off any droid really makes sense for this card because in the prequels, the Jedi were always killing droids left and right.<br />
<br />
Because I wanted the card to mainly be for Yoda, I had originally changed the card to become a two dot rather than still non-unique to keep it from being too broken. That way, you would only have two on the table at once, but it turned out that it really didn&#39;t matter if it was still non-unique.<br />
It is just restricted to &quot;Jedi Masters&quot; alone so that Obi and Luke wouldn&#39;t be able to use it. On the downside, Mundi can&#39;t use it, but it is just one guy out of five possible.<br />
<br />
The next idea for this card was that it would never leave your deck, unless you chose to lose it for a card loss. In other words, if the Jedi using the lightsaber was forfeited, it would go to used pile and not lost pile. This was on the card in place of the Matching Weapon text, which was originally only going to work with Yoda and Mace, but it was decided that it would simply be wrong to always have a lightsaber to pull with Yoda after you got him back with Civil Disorder (V) and re-deployed him. Plus, to make it truly playable, it would have to be pullable with Sai Tor (V).<br />
<br />
The only thing left to worry about was rather or not to have it add to force drains and if so, should it be restricted to where it would work since the card was going to stay non-unique. At first, it did say cumulatively adds to force drains but only at a battleground, but since there were so many cards that got around drains at non-battlegrounds, i.e.<br />
Coward shield, Imperial Decree (V), and Imperial Propaganda (V), it was decided that it didn&#39;t matter. To go along with the drain bonus, the game text for the Jedi Council would have to be ignored. So, after all of the changing and reworking, the card will now be as follows:<br />
<br />
Jedi Lightsaber (V)<br />
<br />
Deploy on a Jedi Master (considered a matching weapon). Cumulatively adds one to Force drain when present. Ignores Dark side game text on Jedi Council. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny (if Yoda defending, draw three). Target hit (lost if target is a droid) and forfeit = 0 if destiny > defense value.<br />
<br />
<br />
Example Deck with my Card<br />
<br />
