<br />
<br />
<br />
Strategy:<br />
<br />
This card will open up a whole new world for the lightside on the ground.<br />
In turn, it gives five more lightsabers that are destiny 2 rather than destiny 1. The biggest reason for this card in your deck will be with Yoda.<br />
It is clear that the main deck design with this card is going to be with Coruscant and Careful Planning (V), so I designed a deck that would work quite well with this new card.<br />
<br />
Try this tech out for size:<br />
<br />
First turn you can pull Yoda, Jedi Master with the Jedi Council, then with Sai Tor (V) give him his matching stick that will be able to drain with at the Council, but more likely, you would want to give him a Lightsaber Proficiency with Rycar (V) and move him over to the Coruscant: Docking Bay to drain for three with Immunity to Attrition, Power 7, defensive value 7, and three destiny swing if you come after him with no fear of 4-Lom with Gun EVER canceling his game text again. You can search for a SAC card during their turn to add even more protection. I play with both versions of Yoda because you might want to play on a different planet. With all of the SAC and Fallen Portals, it will not be an easy victory at any site that Yoda is at.<br />
<br />
The rest of the deck pretty much is designed around Coruscant. The extra docking bays are for getting Celebration going and deploying Luke, JK cheaper and then moving him to Coruscant. With your only battlegrounds being the docking bays, the opponent will always fear the Portal coming down on their head. This is a very defensive deck, where you just sit back and wait for them to come to you. You can leave Yoda at one site and then Qui-Gon or Luke at the other. The two Savrips provide the protection against beatdowns and will in turn provide a lockdown combined with Civil Disorder (V). The K&#39;or Slug (V) keeps you guys on table if the Emperor or Dr. E want to play. Menace Fades and Boushh slow their drains while you continue to hurt them. Mace can drain in the Chamber and cause two damage while Padme is at Yoda&#39;s site. If they are playing a heavy ground deck, get Celebration going, then put all the stick guys, Luke, Yoda, and Qui-Gon at a docking bay with Obi&#39;s Journal to keep them from modifying the drain and with the new ruling would let you cancel two weapon destinies. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/starwarsccg/articles/articles.php?id=6105&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/starwarsccg/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/starwarsccg/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></td></tr></table>
